content: @Robert  Thanks very much for your work on this program.  The "What's New" section says that you have removed the need for internet access permissions, but the install dialog says there is a new "Full Permissions to All Device Features and Storage".  So could you clarify this?
replyContent: Hi Sam, that is the access superuser permission to be compliant with superuser apps. See: https://plus.google.com/103583939320326217147/posts/T9xnMJEnzf1 .  android.permission.ACCESS_SUPERUSER is also used by Jackpal Android Terminal Emulator, so without this permission we would not be able to open Terminal from inside app. Sadly it sounds evil!
